properties.areaDesc: Point Betsie to Sleeping Bear Point MI; Sleeping Bear Point to Grand Traverse Light MI; Manistee to Point Betsie MI; Norwood MI to 5NM West of Mackinac Bridge including Little Traverse Bay
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 2 at 2:44AM EST until February 2 at 10:00PM EST by NWS Gaylord MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...Highest gusts up to 40 kt and highest waves around 7
feet expected.

* WHERE...Norwood MI to 5NM West of Mackinac Bridge including
Little Traverse Bay, Manistee to Point Betsie MI, Sleeping
Bear Point to Grand Traverse Light MI and Point Betsie to
Sleeping Bear Point MI.

* WHEN...From 10 AM this morning to 10 PM EST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous highest waves
which could capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM THIS MORNING TO 10 PM EST THIS EVENING
